  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv Had to check a bit as this was a while ago, but we switched from direct use of `instantsearch.js` to `vue-instantsearch` which removed the `import {...} from \"instantsearch.js\"` statement from our code and made Rollup not have to resolve it (Rollup is configured with `esnext: true` and IIFE as output, not UMD). So we didn't actually change components, just the way it was imported in the app.\r\n\r\nWe now use the `ais-index` and `ais-results` components, with a custom combobox component that uses `algoliaComponent` as a mixin. Composed like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\n<ais-index :app-id=\"...\" :api-key=\"...\" :index-name=\"...\">\r\n    <stuff>...</stuff>\r\n    <custom-combobox (template external but inlined here)>\r\n        <more-stuff>...</more-stuff>\r\n        <ais-results>\r\n            <combo-item>...</combo-item>\r\n        </ais-results>\r\n    </custom-combobox>\r\n</ais-index>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also had to add an Object.assign (and ES Promise) polyfill as we have to support IE 11, but that worked fine with no other changes. Can't point to the repo sadly, but you can check the site here: https://suburbia.io/\r\n\r\nThanks!",
    "created_at": "2018-03-28T16:35:33Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2730#issuecomment-376951925",
